27:10.329 --> 27:12.865
The cave city of Matera

27:12.899 --> 27:16.335
was occupied for a span
of 9,000 years,

27:16.368 --> 27:18.537
predating the days
of Christianity,

27:18.570 --> 27:22.541
the Roman and even Greek
empires.

27:23.676 --> 27:27.146
So this was the shame of Italy,
this place.

27:27.179 --> 27:29.548
It doesn't look shameful to me.

27:29.581 --> 27:32.952
Back in the day, right,
this was where...

27:32.985 --> 27:37.556
Where people lived in caves
and they had no god.

27:39.491 --> 27:41.527
After centuries of neglect,

27:41.560 --> 27:44.563
Matera's cave communities
became, for post-war Italy,

27:44.596 --> 27:48.234
a symbol of national
dysfunction, backwardness,

27:48.267 --> 27:50.737
and horrifying
living conditions.

27:50.770 --> 27:53.840
I mean, this is an area
that was known for briganti,

27:53.873 --> 27:55.507
outlaws, bandits.

27:55.541 --> 27:59.411
This is was always where,
you know, the losers were sent.

28:04.450 --> 28:06.753
Into the '50s and '60s,

28:06.786 --> 28:08.447
this was considered
an embarrassment and a shame.

28:08.454 --> 28:10.256
People lived...

28:10.289 --> 28:11.858
Yeah, because they had
no water, yes.

28:11.891 --> 28:14.393
Ten kids, shitting in a bucket,

28:14.426 --> 28:16.996
up to 50% mortality rate
among children.

28:17.029 --> 28:18.898
Malaria was endemic,

28:18.931 --> 28:21.100
with children begging
in the street

28:21.133 --> 28:22.835
for quinine to prevent it.

28:22.869 --> 28:25.104
They were burning fire
to keep the animals away

28:25.137 --> 28:26.906
as the children were dying.

28:26.939 --> 28:30.609
In the 1950s, the population
was forcibly relocated,

28:30.642 --> 28:33.612
leaving Matera's
cave structures abandoned.

28:33.645 --> 28:34.953
And the way they lived,
you know,

28:34.981 --> 28:36.182
they were still pagan.

28:36.215 --> 28:37.784
And of course now it's...

28:37.817 --> 28:41.553
Because of Mel Gibson
and the Christ movies,

28:41.587 --> 28:44.390
because it looks like Jerusalem
at the time of Christ.

28:44.423 --> 28:46.358
And it's strange that, you know,

28:46.392 --> 28:48.560
in a place that had no god,

28:48.594 --> 28:50.629
they shot all the Christ movies.

28:50.662 --> 28:52.965
Jesus incorporated...
Brought the money,

28:52.999 --> 28:55.067
and all of a sudden,
this became hip,

28:55.101 --> 28:57.536
and people wanted to live
in the caves

28:57.569 --> 29:00.372
and make bed-and-breakfasts
and expensive...

29:00.406 --> 29:02.441
It's expensive to live
in the caves now.

29:02.474 --> 29:03.709
But this is the story

29:03.742 --> 29:05.411
of every beautiful place,
kind of.

29:05.444 --> 29:07.246
It's like, "Let's move
everybody out,"

29:07.279 --> 29:09.648
